cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DB, cs.CY 

The paper deals with generating synthetic data for credit card transactions, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of deep neural nets (cs.AI) and cloud computing (cs.DC) in the field of AI. The paper also discusses the challenges of generating realistic data, which involves domain knowledge and mechanics of credit card processing (cs.DB). Finally, the paper mentions the use of the generated data to train models to predict fraud (cs.CY).
